  "prompt": "Is there an app that gives you recipes based on what you have in the fridge?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several apps designed to provide recipes based on the ingredients you have on hand. Some popular options include:\n\n1. **Cookpad**: This app allows users to search for recipes based on the ingredients they have available. You can enter what you have in your fridge, and it will provide recipe suggestions.\n\n2. **SuperCook**: SuperCook is a completely free recipe discovery app that lets you input the ingredients you have, and it will suggest recipes you can make.\n\n3. **Yummly**: Yummly allows you to filter recipes by available ingredients and offers a smart shopping list for missing ingredients, making meal planning easy.\n\n4. **Epicurious**: This app includes a feature where you can add ingredients you have on hand and find matching recipes.\n\n5. **Allrecipes Dinner Spinner**: You can search for recipes based on the ingredients you have and filter results based on dietary preferences.\n\n6. **Tasty**: Known for its short video recipes, Tasty also has a feature where you can enter ingredients to find suitable recipes.\n\nThese apps can help minimize food waste and make it easier to plan meals around what's already in your fridge.",
